Process Hazard Analysis

Epsilon has a comprehensive Process Hazard Analysis (PHA) program to help ensure that hazards associated with the process are identified and controlled.  Within this program, the process is systematically examined to identify, evaluate and control the hazards involved.

Epsilon uses one or more of the appropriate analysis techniques to perform the PHA evaluations.  The PHA evaluations are performed by a team with expertise in engineering and process operations, and the team includes at least one employee who has experience and knowledge specific to the process being evaluated.  Also, one member of the team must be knowledgeable in the specific PHA methodology being used. The PHA evaluations address:  

